					"title": "Hammock Girl",
					"desc": "This was my final for the Life Drawing and Painting course. At the time I wanted to do something different. No more still-life, I wanted to do something that touches the soul. This painting in particular gives me this nostalgic feeling of a warm afternoon summer. The denseness of the fauna, and the trees, with the sunlight peering through as it slowly fades giving way to a magical summer evening.",
